# Local-only caches and heavy artifacts.
# Anything that documents what happened lives under results/ (whitelisted
# below). Anything that's a re-derivable cache (activations, probe weights,
# per-stimulus tensors) lives under local_data/ and stays out of git.

local_data/
drive_data/
activations/
checkpoints/
data/

# results/ is mostly ignored — see whitelist at bottom of file
results/

# NOTE: figures/ is NOT ignored — we commit publication-ready figures
# so the writeup renders correctly on GitHub.

# Environment
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.pytest_cache/

# Large files (still blocked even under whitelisted dirs)
*.pt
*.safetensors
*.bin
*.npy
*.npz

# OS
.DS_Store

# Claude
.claude/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Whitelist: small documenting artifacts under results/ DO get committed.
# These describe what happened and need to flow through git history so
# the user can see results land in real time and so a fresh clone can
# rebuild the writeup without re-running experiments.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
!results/
!results/**/
!results/**/*.json
!results/**/*.md
!results/**/*.png
!results/**/*.svg
!results/**/*.csv
# concept_vectors.pt is the distilled research artifact — small (1–4 MB
# per model) and consumed by every downstream experiment (geometry,
# steering, parametric). Whitelisting it lets a fresh clone run
# downstream analysis without re-running GPU extraction. The heavy
# per-stimulus activation caches (stimulus_*.pt) remain blocked.
!results/**/concept_vectors.pt
